Fig. 3 shows the two-dimensional valence-electron density color-filled maps of rGO-4-PP Nc in the C1-O1-C2 plane. Obviously, the largest electron distribution area appears around the $\mathrm{O}$ atom, and the narrow electron distribution area appears around the $\mathrm{C}$ atoms. In addition, the maximum valenceelectron density around the $\mathrm{O}$ atom is as high as $\sim 1.15$ a.u. compared with the $\mathrm{C}$ atoms ( $\mathrm{C} 1$ and $\mathrm{C} 2$ ) in the $\mathrm{C}-\mathrm{O}-\mathrm{C}$ linker, which suggests that there is an electron-rich area around the $\mathrm{O}$ atom and there are electron-deficient areas around the adjacent C atoms.

