pollutants compete with the $\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O}_{2}$ to complex with the electrondeficient carbon center, avoiding the useless decomposition of $\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O}_{2}$. Thus, rGO-4-PP Nc shows an excellent performance for pollutant removal. This study offers a new perspective to investigate the potential activity of catalyst theoretically, which is meaningful for finding new metal-free catalyst not only for the Fenton reaction, but also for the other AOPs.

